I think there are some obvious limitations suggested by the description anyway:

It only works on . This is probably not strictly humans, but there are sapients it may not work on. Especially as a result of #3.
It needs to be seen, in it's entirety, so therefore probably doesn't work on somebody with significant visual impairment (although a bas relief version might work by touch or echolocation). It may not work on individuals with significant brain damage to the broca's area (testing is planned).
It probably has probability based limits on the amount of alteration possible, it can't work on entities whose existing personal histories are radically divergent from any possible Foundation employee. This doesn't show up in the testing, because the Foundation hasn't attempted any of these tests.
It is obviously a fairly dangerous Keter-class object in its own right, and abuse has obvious terrible consequences (an AK-class end of the world scenario in which all persons are Foundation employees with 2140/2 clearance).








